1
00:00:08,390 --> 00:00:09,770
Protect it well.

2
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:11,010
That weakness.

3
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:15,900
I'm going to bring him down
and make him pay for what he did.

4
00:00:16,540 --> 00:00:19,230
We'll kick off our plan by
acquiring as many shares as possible.

5
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:20,730
Is something the matter?

6
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:22,780
I just ran into your daughter.

7
00:00:25,170 --> 00:00:27,500
I want you to be my family.

8
00:00:28,050 --> 00:00:29,170
Come live with me.

9
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,229
The boss wants to see you.

10
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:34,720
Move! Hurry!

11
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:37,480
Khun Lené! Khun Rann has disappeared!

12
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:47,060
Still haven't found her?!
What’s taking you so long?!

13
00:00:49,230 --> 00:00:52,110
This is the footage from the front
of the house before it went dead.

14
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,320
It ends right here.

15
00:00:54,660 --> 00:00:55,870
The street camera footage just came in.

16
00:00:56,460 --> 00:00:58,960
But the car that took Khun Rann
disappeared into the tunnel.

17
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:00,690
They might have switched
vehicles along the way.

18
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:04,420
Track every car that went in and out during
that time to see if there are any extra ones.

19
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,150
But there were dozens of cars going in and out.

20
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,320
No matter what it takes! We must find Rann!

21
00:01:10,830 --> 00:01:11,550
Understood.

22
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,289
Dammit!

23
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:20,900
Khun Lené!

24
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:24,390
What is it?! Did you find her?!

25
00:01:25,539 --> 00:01:26,990
Yes, I found her.

26
00:01:30,030 --> 00:01:32,600
What's wrong?
Why are you looking at me like that?

27
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:34,620
Just tell me where she is!

28
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:43,830
Your father contacted me,
saying he’s got work for me to do.

29
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:49,570
You know what it means... don't you?

30
00:01:51,890 --> 00:01:53,500
- My father wants you to—
- Kill Khun Rann.

31
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:59,360
Yes, I think so too.

32
00:02:21,620 --> 00:02:23,010
Where are we going?

33
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:24,920
You don't need to know.

34
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,390
Am I going to die?

35
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:40,270
You didn't blindfold me and even
brought me in through the front door.

36
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:46,030
Don't I at least deserve to know why I'm dying?

37
00:02:47,850 --> 00:02:48,800
You'll find out soon enough.

38
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:04,900
Calm down. It's okay.
You're prepared for this, Rann.

39
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,410
Stay focused.

40
00:03:07,170 --> 00:03:09,030
We just met not long ago, Noo Rann.

41
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,530
But you look an absolute mess.

42
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,280
Khun Kanin.

43
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:25,290
Yes, it's me.

44
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:30,990
But it seems you already knew it was me.

45
00:03:33,610 --> 00:03:34,560
What do you want?

46
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,550
I should be the one asking you that.

47
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:53,370
But you don't seem surprised at all
as to why you're here.

48
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,440
What are you going to do to me?

49
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:04,740
A smart girl like you...
should be able to figure it out.

50
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,270
Killing me won't do you any good.

51
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:14,750
I'm not a significant variable
between you and Khun Lené.

52
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,700
Are you sure?

53
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:30,940
If you're not important,

54
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:36,180
why did my daughter send you
all the way to the other side of the world?

55
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:40,760
No.

56
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,960
I was just her junior in university.

57
00:04:45,330 --> 00:04:46,380
You already know that.

58
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:51,850
A junior… who dares to dig up
information right under my nose?

59
00:04:54,610 --> 00:04:57,250
I truly admire your courage.

60
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:03,540
So, what did you manage to get?

61
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:24,800
That's fine.

62
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,560
You don't have to answer.

63
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:31,450
Since you said earlier
that you aren't important...

64
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:35,980
let me make you a bit more important, then.

65
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:41,330
Like using you to teach
my cocky daughter a lesson

66
00:05:41,909 --> 00:05:44,409
that she shouldn't mess with her own father.

67
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:46,730
Sound good?

68
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,640
Go in and buy us as much time as possible.

69
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:20,280
Once our people are ready,
I'll give you the signal.

70
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:22,660
Count on it.

71
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,740
You know what I'm capable of.

72
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:30,270
Peem.

73
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:33,690
No matter what happens, Rann must be safe.

74
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:38,179
Yes, I know.

75
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,740
Promise me.
No matter what my father orders you to do.

76
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:46,990
I only take orders from you.

77
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:50,280
Don't you remember the oath I took?

78
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:54,460
And it will always be that way... boss.

79
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:06,300
I'm going in alone now.

80
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:08,760
Wish me luck?

81
00:09:09,470 --> 00:09:10,310
Don’t die.

82
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:12,690
Copy that.

83
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,600
Hey! Who goes there?

84
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:22,270
Relax. It’s me.

85
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:27,290
You're always like this.
Forgot who your senior is?

86
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:33,510
Everyone, get into position.
Wait for my signal.

87
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:34,660
Copy that. In position.

88
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:50,540
While we wait,

89
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:53,690
why don't we find something to talk about?

90
00:09:57,460 --> 00:09:59,810
Like, a bedtime story.

91
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:02,150
A story about

92
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:07,720
an ungrateful daughter who
plans to get rid of her own father.

93
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,890
Once upon a time...

94
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:16,510
there was a father.

95
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:20,370
He worked his fingers to the bone,

96
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:26,750
earning money to build everything for his family.

97
00:10:28,090 --> 00:10:31,640
As his daughter grew up,

98
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:38,090
he noticed how smart and sharp she was.

99
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:44,460
Truly worthy of taking over his work.

100
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:50,290
Even though she was only ten years old.

101
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:57,350
That's just how a father is, I suppose.

102
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,990
Except she inherited her mother's stubbornness.

103
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,490
Filled with nothing but naive thinking.

104
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,870
The father hoped that one day, she’d realize...

105
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:25,660
everything she has today is
because of the very business she hates.

106
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,560
So that’s why you killed P’ Le’s mother.

107
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:41,730
It was merely an accidental killing,
nothing more.

108
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:45,490
That is exactly why P’ Le hates you.

109
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,030
You kill people.

110
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:55,270
Then how do you explain her killing my people?

111
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:59,480
She really isn't that different
from her father, after all.

112
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:04,910
She only believes what she chooses to believe.

113
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,710
Doing whatever it takes to reach the goal.

114
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:11,650
Even if it means hurting others or…

115
00:12:13,710 --> 00:12:15,790
leaving them behind.

116
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:27,640
Even I was...

117
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:32,930
shocked by how close she came to outsmarting me.

118
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,260
She almost had me removed from the board.

119
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:42,760
But unfortunately…
she chose to trust the wrong person.

120
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:59,540
Thank you so much
for giving me that extra leverage.

121
00:13:01,430 --> 00:13:03,780
So that I won’t have to
deal with my own daughter.

122
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:12,210
The moral of this story is...

123
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:20,580
my daughter should never
have crossed me, her father.

124
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:25,800
Otherwise... everyone around her

125
00:13:26,850 --> 00:13:29,300
will be eliminated,
until there is no one left.

126
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:37,100
So, what do you think of this punishment?

127
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:40,760
P’ Le, I’m sorry.

128
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:44,790
I'm sorry I haven't told you anything yet.

129
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:51,360
If I ever get another chance,
I will tell you everything.

130
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:55,570
Bang!

131
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:02,900
Just in time.
I've been waiting for you.

132
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:09,680
What's going on here?

133
00:14:10,330 --> 00:14:11,440
Did I miss something?

134
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:17,530
Take care of it.

135
00:14:24,410 --> 00:14:25,160
Why?

136
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:29,240
Did you grow attached to her as a co-worker?

137
00:14:33,770 --> 00:14:37,670
Come on, Khun Kanin.
Please don't play these kinds of jokes on me.

138
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,390
Then do it.

139
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,370
Out of all people...

140
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:52,340
why does it have to be me?

141
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,340
You know I don't like
getting blood on my clothes.

142
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:15,540
Do you know what lesson I want
to teach my daughter the most?

143
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,130
Your most trusted person…

144
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:25,060
could kill the person you love the most...

145
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:27,580
at any moment.

146
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:16,430
Looks like we need to hurry up.

147
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:30,330
Peem, stall for time. I'm on my way in.

148
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:05,730
If we act right now...
won't everything we've done go to waste?

149
00:17:06,790 --> 00:17:08,790
She doesn't have the guts to kill her own father.

150
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:10,920
But this time, Khun Lené won't let it slide.

151
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:13,280
And what can she possibly do?

152
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,369
Shoot her!

153
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:21,819
Peem, I'm coming up.
Don't do anything to Rann.

154
00:17:47,170 --> 00:17:48,170
Shoot her.

155
00:17:48,710 --> 00:17:49,410
No!

156
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,500
I've got Rann.

157
00:18:34,410 --> 00:18:36,700
Get Khun Rann out of here.
I’ll hold them off for you.

158
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:41,100
I'm okay.

159
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,180
Trust me.

160
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:45,180
Go!

161
00:18:53,370 --> 00:18:54,990
Don't look back! Keep running!

162
00:18:55,010 --> 00:18:55,850
But P’ Peem—

163
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:58,700
Save yourself first.
Peem can handle himself.

164
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:19,310
I figured it would turn out like this…. Dad.

165
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:24,010
But I never imagined it would end this way.

166
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:01,950
What would you two do...
without a head bodyguard like me?

167
00:20:18,430 --> 00:20:20,170
Peem! Peem!

168
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:21,670
Peem!

169
00:20:23,050 --> 00:20:23,840
Peem!

170
00:20:24,650 --> 00:20:25,450
Peem!

171
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:26,880
No.

172
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:28,640
No!

173
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,690
No!

174
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:10,330
Yesterday evening, a fire broke out
at a warehouse near the port,

175
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:12,910
which serves as a major cargo storage facility.

176
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:18,400
The fire spread rapidly, sending
thick plumes of smoke into the sky

177
00:21:18,430 --> 00:21:21,670
and causing panic among nearby residents.

178
00:21:22,130 --> 00:21:25,520
The incident has left numerous people injured,

179
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:29,290
and at least three fatalities have been reported.

180
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:34,390
One of the confirmed fatalities
is Khun Kanin Asawachun,

181
00:21:34,410 --> 00:21:38,630
a board member of a major
Thai shipping company.

182
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:41,860
He was trapped beneath the building's
debris and was unable to escape in time.

183
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:46,850
Rescue teams spent several hours battling
the blaze before bringing it under control.

184
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:51,750
The authorities speculate that
the fire was caused by a short circuit,

185
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:55,190
and a more thorough check is currently underway.

186
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:59,590
We will bring you further updates
as soon as they become available.

187
00:22:13,050 --> 00:22:16,210
It's time, P’ Le. We have to go.

188
00:22:32,530 --> 00:22:35,460
Mm. Let’s go.

189
00:22:53,130 --> 00:22:54,930
I finally understand that dream.

190
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,180
It wasn't P’ Le.

191
00:23:01,370 --> 00:23:02,370
It was you.

192
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:32,830
I’m okay, Rann.

193
00:23:34,670 --> 00:23:35,610
I’m okay.

194
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:51,630
If you don't watch your mouth,
your whole body will be riddled with holes.

195
00:23:51,650 --> 00:23:52,830
As long as I don't die…

196
00:23:53,820 --> 00:23:56,440
I don't mind a couple of extra holes.

197
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,330
You're not a servant.

198
00:24:04,220 --> 00:24:05,740
You're like a big brother to me.

199
00:24:06,210 --> 00:24:07,470
I'm going in alone now.

200
00:24:08,870 --> 00:24:09,920
Wish me luck?

201
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:11,190
Don’t die.

202
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:13,770
Copy that.

203
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:17,940
What would you two do...
without a head bodyguard like me?

204
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:50,620
Go to bed. Aren't you sleepy?

205
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,340
You're not sleeping either.

206
00:25:01,260 --> 00:25:02,170
Rann.

207
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,780
I’m fine.

208
00:25:09,010 --> 00:25:10,430
I see nothing at all.

209
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,530
I'm going to stay right here.

210
00:25:16,690 --> 00:25:18,590
Because I want you to know…

211
00:25:20,630 --> 00:25:22,200
you're not alone.

212
00:25:36,530 --> 00:25:38,820
You mean besides the dozens of house staff?

213
00:26:07,770 --> 00:26:08,790
You know what, Rann?

214
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,240
Peem was the one who always stood by my side.

215
00:26:18,270 --> 00:26:19,650
He was like family.

216
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,670
An older brother.

217
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:26,470
The boy my mother saved all those years ago.

218
00:26:30,370 --> 00:26:34,600
Peem told me that he’d be
nothing without my mother.

219
00:26:38,150 --> 00:26:42,660
He would do anything for me...
for my late mother.

220
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:50,610
And we shared a single goal…

221
00:26:51,420 --> 00:26:53,000
...to take down my father together.

222
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,510
But why?

223
00:26:59,780 --> 00:27:02,090
Why am I the only one who survived?

224
00:27:03,390 --> 00:27:06,720
Why does it feel so empty now that it's all over?

225
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:10,800
Why did my brother have to die?!

226
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:18,440
Rann…

227
00:27:20,660 --> 00:27:23,720
If it had been me instead,
would it all be over?

228
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:27,400
Why did Peem have to die in my place?!

229
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:31,020
It's all my fault!

230
00:27:37,690 --> 00:27:38,640
P’ Le.

231
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:42,460
Please don't say that.

232
00:27:43,610 --> 00:27:47,480
If P’ Peem heard this,
how sad do you think he'd be?

233
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:53,300
Besides, have you forgotten?

234
00:27:55,010 --> 00:27:57,230
Have you forgotten about me?

235
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:03,830
If you die... then what about me?

236
00:28:06,710 --> 00:28:08,850
You’re my whole world.

237
00:28:17,860 --> 00:28:20,450
I came back to fix everything...

238
00:28:25,100 --> 00:28:27,620
just so you could live again.

239
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,530
What do you mean, you came back?

240
00:28:53,740 --> 00:28:55,150
I have something to confess.

241
00:29:01,550 --> 00:29:05,000
So you're saying you got my letter,

242
00:29:06,630 --> 00:29:10,770
came back to Thailand,
only to find out that I'd been shot dead?

243
00:29:11,510 --> 00:29:15,840
And then Thana killed you, which
triggered you to return to the beginning?

244
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:18,360
Is that it?

245
00:29:18,750 --> 00:29:20,430
You don't have to believe me, P’ Le.

246
00:29:23,090 --> 00:29:24,520
I just wanted you to know.

247
00:29:27,110 --> 00:29:29,320
I just wrote you a letter last week.

248
00:29:33,790 --> 00:29:35,000
It was…

249
00:29:36,930 --> 00:29:41,130
‘I hope you’re always happy,’ wasn’t it?

250
00:29:57,510 --> 00:29:59,490
You don’t have to believe me.

251
00:30:02,340 --> 00:30:06,140
Maybe it was nothing more
than a long dream I had.

252
00:30:09,780 --> 00:30:10,980
Nine years?

253
00:30:14,930 --> 00:30:15,750
Huh?

254
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:23,010
That means... you've been
waiting for me for nine years?

255
00:30:25,620 --> 00:30:30,250
The five years we were apart,
and the four years since you came back.

256
00:30:39,570 --> 00:30:40,570
I’m sorry.

257
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:43,930
Why are you apologizing to me?

258
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:49,140
I always thought you were happy.

259
00:30:50,700 --> 00:30:51,850
I never thought...

260
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,070
everything I did...

261
00:31:10,450 --> 00:31:12,330
Could you give me another chance?

262
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:19,200
Let me fix everything this time.

263
00:31:20,650 --> 00:31:21,700
It’s my turn.

264
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:27,680
I will do whatever it takes to stay by your side.

265
00:31:38,090 --> 00:31:39,190
Don't leave me.

266
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:44,460
Don’t push me away again.

267
00:31:48,210 --> 00:31:51,420
If I ever do that, you can kill me.

268
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:54,120
I won't kill you.

269
00:31:55,490 --> 00:31:56,670
I won't let you die either.

270
00:32:19,110 --> 00:32:20,470
Get out of my sight.

271
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,250
If you want to keep her around…

272
00:33:09,380 --> 00:33:11,400
it’s still not too late to
go after her now, boss.

273
00:33:18,270 --> 00:33:19,540
To do that...

274
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:26,370
I need to be sure it's
completely safe around me first.

275
00:33:33,340 --> 00:33:34,350
I’ll help you.

276
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:40,230
I want to see you happy too, boss.

277
00:33:45,770 --> 00:33:47,050
You have to be happy.

278
00:33:54,970 --> 00:33:58,330
You don't actually have the heart
to send her back anyway, do you?

279
00:33:58,570 --> 00:33:59,620
Know-it-all!

280
00:34:00,340 --> 00:34:02,100
Would you look at that smile?

281
00:34:03,490 --> 00:34:05,320
Oop! Heh, missed me!

282
00:34:08,670 --> 00:34:10,100
Then you should know

283
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:14,400
that this brother is more than
willing to help his little sister.

284
00:35:31,550 --> 00:35:34,810
Thank you… for everything.

285
00:35:39,450 --> 00:35:40,810
I'll be happy.

286
00:35:42,630 --> 00:35:45,150
For both of us, P' Peem.

287
00:36:20,860 --> 00:36:24,580
Rise and shine… baby.

288
00:36:34,250 --> 00:36:35,470
Won't wake up?

289
00:36:36,590 --> 00:36:38,710
Does that mean you want a morning kiss?

290
00:36:45,670 --> 00:36:46,560
P’ Le.

291
00:36:49,310 --> 00:36:50,320
Are you okay?

292
00:36:52,100 --> 00:36:54,610
How could I not be okay, hmm?

293
00:36:55,290 --> 00:36:58,320
- Well…
- I just wanted to wake up my girlfriend.

294
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:29,860
Don't you like this?

295
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:39,840
I do.

296
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:42,570
What was that?

297
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:45,290
I said, I like it.

298
00:37:47,450 --> 00:37:51,640
If you like it...
look into my eyes when you say it.

299
00:38:01,470 --> 00:38:02,400
I like it.

300
00:38:03,350 --> 00:38:04,450
And what else?

301
00:38:05,980 --> 00:38:07,580
I like it when you speak softly to me.

302
00:38:08,550 --> 00:38:09,480
And what else?

303
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:12,390
I like it when you wake me up.

304
00:38:13,910 --> 00:38:14,850
Hmm?

305
00:38:16,510 --> 00:38:18,860
And I’ll like it even more…

306
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:24,270
If you…

307
00:38:32,510 --> 00:38:33,520
kiss me.

308
00:38:56,930 --> 00:38:59,030
You have a lunch meeting
with the shareholders today,

309
00:38:59,060 --> 00:39:00,540
followed by a meeting.

310
00:39:01,650 --> 00:39:03,110
That's all for today's schedule.

311
00:39:03,730 --> 00:39:05,570
And don't forget the documents I asked for.

312
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:08,300
Yes, I'll bring them to
your office right away.

313
00:39:12,910 --> 00:39:14,590
- Nong Rann, hold on!
- Nong Rann.

314
00:39:16,900 --> 00:39:18,300
How’s the situation?

315
00:39:19,340 --> 00:39:20,350
What do you mean?

316
00:39:20,420 --> 00:39:23,520
You know, the warehouse
fire was already bad,

317
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:25,320
but now the stock prices are crashing.

318
00:39:25,340 --> 00:39:27,030
Plus, with Khun Kanin passing away,

319
00:39:27,050 --> 00:39:29,960
the whole company feels
like a total war zone now!

320
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:31,330
And there’s Khun Peem too.

321
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:32,390
I know, right?

322
00:39:32,570 --> 00:39:34,870
To think Khun Peem went
in to rescue Khun Kanin,

323
00:39:34,890 --> 00:39:36,420
only for them to get trapped inside.

324
00:39:37,430 --> 00:39:38,660
And look at Khun Lené.

325
00:39:38,690 --> 00:39:41,940
She's suddenly acting like she’s fine.
I can't help but worry about her.

326
00:39:43,730 --> 00:39:47,370
Clients, shareholders, and the media...

327
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:50,190
Why does it all have to fall
on our boss’ shoulders, Sis?

328
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:53,040
We just can't help but worry.

329
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:02,280
This means the situation is now under control.

330
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:05,250
All right, let's proceed.

331
00:40:05,290 --> 00:40:07,180
I will bring this matter
up in our next meeting.

332
00:40:07,350 --> 00:40:08,360
- Yes, ma’am.
- Understood.

333
00:40:14,890 --> 00:40:17,090
Everyone, what are we going to do?

334
00:40:17,110 --> 00:40:18,480
Calm down. What's wrong?

335
00:40:18,510 --> 00:40:21,190
Just now… I just saw Khun Lené—

336
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:22,900
Oh? What? Tell us!

337
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:24,410
She was crying!

338
00:40:24,430 --> 00:40:25,390
- What?!
- What?!

339
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:29,000
I'm serious, I'm not lying!
I saw it with my own eyes.

340
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:30,630
She was wiping away her tears like this!

341
00:40:31,550 --> 00:40:33,090
What should we do, Sis?

342
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:37,950
Khun Lené must be devastated over
losing both her father and Khun Peem.

343
00:40:38,780 --> 00:40:40,200
I feel so bad for her.

344
00:40:40,860 --> 00:40:42,880
- How should we comfort her?
- Yeah.

345
00:40:43,260 --> 00:40:45,820
I've never seen her this down before.

346
00:40:46,020 --> 00:40:47,620
How can we comfort her?

347
00:40:47,650 --> 00:40:51,540
We're just lowly employees.
All we can do is make sure we earn our paycheck.

348
00:40:51,770 --> 00:40:54,210
But at least Khun Lené still has Nong Rann.

349
00:40:54,510 --> 00:40:56,900
Nong Rann, please take care of Khun Lené.

350
00:40:56,930 --> 00:40:59,430
If there's anything we can do, just let us know.

351
00:41:04,080 --> 00:41:05,680
- I'm tired from running.
- Want some water?

352
00:41:17,990 --> 00:41:18,990
Hold on, P’ Le.

353
00:41:26,710 --> 00:41:27,630
What is it?

354
00:41:28,730 --> 00:41:30,150
This is the office.

355
00:41:32,580 --> 00:41:33,500
I know.

356
00:41:34,980 --> 00:41:36,250
If you know, then stop.

357
00:41:39,050 --> 00:41:39,900
No.

358
00:41:55,190 --> 00:41:57,310
We’re doing OT right now.

359
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,980
This is not that kind of OT.

360
00:42:01,180 --> 00:42:03,110
Then like I said...

361
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:06,180
Not. Stopping.

362
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:09,950
Let's talk first.

363
00:42:12,690 --> 00:42:16,190
Do you know that everyone
is worried about you right now?

364
00:42:42,900 --> 00:42:45,190
P’ Le, do you know…

365
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:46,890
Know what?

366
00:42:47,980 --> 00:42:49,390
...that you're so sly?

367
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:52,350
When was I ever like that?

368
00:42:54,220 --> 00:42:55,530
Right now.

369
00:42:56,430 --> 00:43:00,110
Everyone thinks you're devastated about P’ Peem,

370
00:43:00,550 --> 00:43:02,130
and that you’ve been crying.

371
00:43:03,890 --> 00:43:05,620
But how could I not know...

372
00:43:06,530 --> 00:43:10,020
that you just didn’t get
enough sleep last night?

373
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:15,570
But doing this with me in the office?

374
00:43:18,820 --> 00:43:20,290
I am sad.

375
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:26,100
But I know Peem wouldn't want me to be like that.

376
00:43:27,830 --> 00:43:31,130
If it were Peem, he'd be teasing me…

377
00:43:31,770 --> 00:43:33,360
telling me to move on,

378
00:43:34,490 --> 00:43:36,230
saying there's still so much to be done.

379
00:43:36,970 --> 00:43:39,130
How could I keep wallowing in sadness?

380
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:41,630
He’d laugh his head off at me.

381
00:44:01,090 --> 00:44:02,690
Do you understand now?

382
00:44:09,830 --> 00:44:10,720
Hold on.

383
00:44:11,560 --> 00:44:12,330
What?

384
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:14,850
I thought we were done talking.

385
00:44:19,590 --> 00:44:20,820
But…

386
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:27,260
I’ve already locked the door.

387
00:44:34,590 --> 00:44:35,570
May I?

388
00:48:22,110 --> 00:48:24,770
Sleepy? You can sleep if you want.

389
00:48:27,570 --> 00:48:28,560
I can't.

390
00:48:28,940 --> 00:48:31,460
We need to go home,
or P' Dia might get worried.

391
00:48:32,250 --> 00:48:34,310
Just sleep. I'll take you home.

392
00:48:37,270 --> 00:48:38,520
Are you going to carry me?

393
00:48:40,450 --> 00:48:42,130
You think I can't carry you?

394
00:48:44,250 --> 00:48:45,260
You’re right.

395
00:48:46,090 --> 00:48:47,570
You did get heavier.

396
00:48:48,160 --> 00:48:51,300
I almost threw my back out lifting you earlier.

397
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:55,250
Take that!
Forget about carrying me, then.

398
00:48:59,030 --> 00:49:00,840
But I want to carry you.

399
00:49:23,180 --> 00:49:24,120
P’ Le.

400
00:49:24,680 --> 00:49:25,580
Hm?

401
00:49:27,330 --> 00:49:28,660
What if people find out?

402
00:49:31,140 --> 00:49:34,630
Let them. It'll back them off.

403
00:49:36,970 --> 00:49:40,590
I know how often those
HR folks come to talk to you.

404
00:49:43,810 --> 00:49:45,760
But I only talk to them about work.

405
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:49,400
You’re the one who should stop being fierce.

406
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:54,600
There’s no need for you
to isolate yourself anymore.

407
00:49:56,390 --> 00:49:59,080
And no need to be afraid of
getting close to anyone anymore.

408
00:50:08,340 --> 00:50:09,350
True.

409
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:14,310
I don't have to worry about my father
ruining anyone just to warn me anymore.

410
00:50:18,610 --> 00:50:19,620
But...

411
00:50:22,290 --> 00:50:24,130
would it really be okay if I…

412
00:50:28,060 --> 00:50:29,070
get close to others?

413
00:50:32,790 --> 00:50:33,670
Why?

414
00:50:39,770 --> 00:50:43,640
Aren't you afraid that
others will fall for my charms?

415
00:50:44,980 --> 00:50:49,570
Because I'm both beautiful and...

416
00:50:50,690 --> 00:50:51,700
…very rich.

417
00:50:58,150 --> 00:50:59,150
So, what's it gonna be?

418
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:04,080
Do you really want me to
get close to others, Noo Rann?

419
00:51:05,250 --> 00:51:06,030
Hm?

420
00:51:16,760 --> 00:51:18,330
Just a tiny bit is enough.

421
00:51:19,320 --> 00:51:21,350
Didn’t you want me to be
close to my subordinates?

422
00:51:39,150 --> 00:51:40,130
I'm jealous.

423
00:51:44,710 --> 00:51:45,870
Careful...

424
00:51:47,990 --> 00:51:49,840
or I'm going to nibble you back.

425
00:51:51,220 --> 00:51:52,260
Go ahead then.

426
00:51:56,690 --> 00:51:58,500
But you're not allowed to nibble anyone else.

427
00:52:15,370 --> 00:52:18,290
‘I hope you’re always happy.’

428
00:52:21,790 --> 00:52:23,520
You've waited for so many years.

429
00:52:25,020 --> 00:52:27,060
It's time for me to make this come true.

430
00:52:42,570 --> 00:52:45,670
‘Meet me here tonight at 10 PM.’

431
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:50,680
Are you Khun Rann?

432
00:52:50,830 --> 00:52:52,510
Uh, yes, that’s me.

433
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:54,590
Right this way, please.

434
00:52:54,620 --> 00:52:57,060
The other guest has arrived
and is waiting for you.

435
00:52:57,980 --> 00:52:59,220
- This way, please.
- Thank you.

436
00:53:00,500 --> 00:53:02,290
Here is your table.
Please have a seat.

437
00:53:02,580 --> 00:53:03,580
Thank you.

438
00:53:10,510 --> 00:53:11,510
P’ Le.

439
00:53:17,540 --> 00:53:18,680
Are you surprised?

440
00:53:20,490 --> 00:53:24,520
I racked my brain trying to figure out
what would make you happy.

441
00:53:25,680 --> 00:53:27,170
But this was all I could think of.

442
00:53:32,910 --> 00:53:33,700
For you.

443
00:53:36,990 --> 00:53:37,940
Thank you.

444
00:53:50,340 --> 00:53:51,270
Thank you.

445
00:53:54,080 --> 00:53:56,030
Thank you for staying by my side.

446
00:53:58,150 --> 00:53:59,270
Just having you here...

447
00:54:01,290 --> 00:54:03,480
is more than I could ever dream of.

448
00:54:20,430 --> 00:54:22,640
No matter how many times you turn back time,

449
00:54:24,380 --> 00:54:25,960
I will always be right here.

450
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:28,710
No matter how many lives I live...

451
00:54:31,540 --> 00:54:32,980
my love for you will never change.

452
00:54:47,310 --> 00:54:50,550
~ Since the moment of my return ~

453
00:54:50,570 --> 00:54:53,860
~ I realized I came back for you ~

454
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:56,530
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

455
00:54:56,560 --> 00:55:00,460
~ For the day I left you all alone ~

456
00:55:00,490 --> 00:55:07,350
~ From now on, I’ll never let you slip away ~

457
00:55:07,370 --> 00:55:10,520
~ With every breath I take ~

458
00:55:11,230 --> 00:55:15,800
~ I’ll make up to you for the time we lost ~

459
00:55:18,540 --> 00:55:19,980
You are my one…

460
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:24,650
and only.

461
00:55:42,750 --> 00:55:44,720
You are my whole world, Rann.

462
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:03,600
P’ Le…

463
00:56:13,780 --> 00:56:14,790
Did you wait long?

464
00:56:33,740 --> 00:56:36,970
Stay still! Don't move!
Don't go anywhere.

465
00:56:39,490 --> 00:56:41,690
What if you trip, fall flat
on your face, and die?

466
00:57:02,070 --> 00:57:03,630
Does this mean I survived?

467
00:57:05,390 --> 00:57:06,300
Mmhmm.

468
00:57:10,090 --> 00:57:11,690
Don’t cry, baby.

469
00:57:18,670 --> 00:57:20,500
There, there. It’s okay.

470
00:57:23,190 --> 00:57:26,430
I was scared. So scared.

471
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:30,110
I don't ever want to go through that again.

472
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:36,060
I'm not going to die.

473
00:57:37,130 --> 00:57:39,390
I won't let anyone take my Noo Rann away from me.

474
00:57:39,970 --> 00:57:40,680
Okay?

475
00:57:42,820 --> 00:57:43,710
C’mere.

476
00:57:47,320 --> 00:57:48,550
It’s okay.

477
00:57:53,330 --> 00:57:54,730
It’s okay, it’s okay.

478
00:57:56,110 --> 00:57:57,230
It’s okay.

479
00:57:59,450 --> 00:58:00,660
Let me see your face.

480
00:58:01,610 --> 00:58:04,900
Gosh, your makeup is ruined.

481
00:58:06,680 --> 00:58:08,440
Come on, P’ Le…

482
00:58:08,470 --> 00:58:09,970
It’s okay, it’s okay.

483
00:58:12,930 --> 00:58:14,300
It’s okay, it’s okay.

484
00:58:40,220 --> 00:58:41,390
I’m sorry.

485
00:58:49,950 --> 00:58:50,820
Here you go.

486
00:58:55,130 --> 00:58:55,940
Thank you.

487
00:59:03,090 --> 00:59:06,340
- Hey, did you see that? Khun Lené…
- She smiled!

488
00:59:06,870 --> 00:59:08,460
- Isn’t it weird?
- Totally.

489
00:59:10,280 --> 00:59:11,560
Did you see that, P’ Le?

490
00:59:12,260 --> 00:59:13,860
Everyone was completely stunned.

491
00:59:16,490 --> 00:59:19,500
They're probably saying that
since Noo Rann came along,

492
00:59:19,810 --> 00:59:21,740
Khun Lené has gotten a whole lot nicer.

493
00:59:22,980 --> 00:59:26,710
Which means I can’t let
my Noo Rann go ever again.

494
00:59:27,590 --> 00:59:28,440
Right?

495
00:59:30,560 --> 00:59:33,290
My, aren't you flattering yourself?

496
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:34,860
I'm being serious.

497
00:59:48,520 --> 00:59:51,110
Looks like I can’t live without
you anymore, Noo Rann.

498
00:59:54,640 --> 00:59:56,420
I don't want to be home alone,

499
00:59:57,160 --> 00:59:58,880
I don't want to go places alone,

500
00:59:59,960 --> 01:00:02,070
and I certainly don't want to go on trips alone.

501
01:00:14,690 --> 01:00:16,580
I want to have you by my side

502
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,460
for the rest of my life.

503
01:00:23,360 --> 01:00:24,360
So...

504
01:00:53,410 --> 01:00:54,640
will you marry me?

505
01:00:56,840 --> 01:01:00,040
~ Since the moment of my return ~

506
01:01:00,070 --> 01:01:03,360
~ I realized I came back for you ~

507
01:01:03,380 --> 01:01:06,040
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

508
01:01:06,070 --> 01:01:09,960
~ For the day I left you all alone ~

509
01:01:09,980 --> 01:01:16,900
~ From now on, I’ll never let you slip away ~

510
01:01:14,180 --> 01:01:15,180
Yes!

511
01:01:16,930 --> 01:01:20,060
~ With every breath I take ~

512
01:01:17,610 --> 01:01:18,610
I'll marry you.

513
01:01:20,780 --> 01:01:25,260
~ I’ll make up to you for the time we lost ~

514
01:01:20,810 --> 01:01:22,590
You can't take back your proposal.

515
01:02:02,750 --> 01:02:04,760
- Why are you crying, Sis?
- I’m jealous!

516
01:02:05,720 --> 01:02:08,040
~ I’m so grateful for every moment ~

517
01:02:08,070 --> 01:02:10,350
~ Now that I have you in my arms ~

518
01:02:10,370 --> 01:02:12,360
~ Whether in dreams or in my fantasies ~

519
01:02:12,380 --> 01:02:15,790
~ You're the only one I see there ~

520
01:02:15,820 --> 01:02:17,520
~ Hold my hand a little tighter ~

521
01:02:17,550 --> 01:02:19,470
~ From now on, I won't let go ~

522
01:02:19,490 --> 01:02:26,190
~ Oh darling, please don’t ever disappear again ~

523
01:02:57,350 --> 01:02:59,060
What are you so happy about?

524
01:03:02,440 --> 01:03:03,760
Well, aren’t you happy, P’ Le?

525
01:03:04,660 --> 01:03:06,420
We're officially married now!

526
01:03:07,270 --> 01:03:10,110
Even the district officer gave us their blessings.

527
01:03:11,870 --> 01:03:13,470
How could I not be?

528
01:03:14,990 --> 01:03:18,750
After all... you're finally mine.

529
01:03:22,950 --> 01:03:23,750
Says who?

530
01:03:24,360 --> 01:03:25,030
Huh?

531
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:29,000
You're the one who belongs to me.

532
01:03:31,850 --> 01:03:32,980
Is that how it is?

533
01:03:35,420 --> 01:03:39,210
From now on, I won’t have to worry
about you breaking your promise.

534
01:03:40,980 --> 01:03:45,910
If you don't fly to me, I'll just
use your money to fly right to you!

535
01:03:48,550 --> 01:03:50,160
Already planning to spend my money?

536
01:03:52,600 --> 01:03:54,450
Can’t I?

537
01:03:56,070 --> 01:03:56,780
Hm?

538
01:03:59,730 --> 01:04:01,040
Who said you couldn’t?

539
01:04:03,260 --> 01:04:04,550
This P’ Le…

540
01:04:06,140 --> 01:04:09,090
will give you her body, her soul,

541
01:04:10,330 --> 01:04:11,940
her bank accounts, and her title.

542
01:04:13,650 --> 01:04:14,840
Including all your cars.

543
01:04:17,370 --> 01:04:20,050
Yes, including all the cars.

544
01:04:22,960 --> 01:04:26,850
And every corner of your heart too.

545
01:04:32,160 --> 01:04:33,080
Fair enough.

546
01:04:34,940 --> 01:04:36,370
But…

547
01:04:37,620 --> 01:04:39,810
Wait. There's a 'but'?

548
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:44,490
Hm?

549
01:04:44,820 --> 01:04:46,390
You have to kiss me first.

550
01:04:52,100 --> 01:04:55,550
Can you do that... my dear wife?

551
01:05:06,070 --> 01:05:07,090
Again, please.

552
01:05:09,110 --> 01:05:10,070
What?

553
01:05:10,670 --> 01:05:13,130
You mean, ‘my dear wife’?

554
01:05:19,730 --> 01:05:22,130
~ I’m so grateful for every moment ~

555
01:05:22,160 --> 01:05:24,470
~ Now that I have you in my arms ~

556
01:05:24,500 --> 01:05:26,500
~ Whether in dreams or in my fantasies ~

557
01:05:26,520 --> 01:05:29,940
~ You're the only one I see there ~

558
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:31,620
~ Hold my hand a little tighter ~

559
01:05:31,640 --> 01:05:33,600
~ From now on, I won't let go ~

560
01:05:33,630 --> 01:05:40,340
~ Oh darling, please don’t ever disappear again ~

561
01:05:40,470 --> 01:05:43,100
Yes, my dear wife.

562
01:05:45,240 --> 01:05:47,670
~ I’m so grateful for every moment ~

563
01:05:47,700 --> 01:05:49,980
~ Now that I have you in my arms ~

564
01:05:48,250 --> 01:05:49,540
You're getting too good at this.

565
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:51,970
~ Whether in dreams or in my fantasies ~

566
01:05:50,270 --> 01:05:51,230
What?

567
01:05:51,990 --> 01:05:55,370
~ You're the only one I see there ~

568
01:05:55,400 --> 01:05:57,130
~ Hold my hand a little tighter ~

569
01:05:57,160 --> 01:05:59,130
~ From now on, I won't let go ~

570
01:05:59,150 --> 01:06:05,990
~ Oh darling, please don’t ever disappear again ~

571
01:06:06,020 --> 01:06:08,270
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.
